The vehicle that the MCA was driving.[Stephen Nzioka, Standard]  Makueni Member of the County Assembly has died after he was involved in a road accident.  Harris Ngui Musau MCA for Nguu-Masumba Ward died in the Mombasa-Nairobi highway on Tuesday, June 15.  He was on his way to Makueni county when his car collided with an oncoming Sharkman truck headed in Mombasa direction killing him on the spot.  The few minutes to 7 pm accident left the county legislator's white Prado written off with the dashboard completely disfigured.  Mukaa Sub-county Police Commander Jacinta Mwarania said the accident took place in the Salama area along the busy highway.  “The deceased was in the company of another unknown female passenger who sustained serious head injuries and was rushed to Machakos Level Five Hospital,” Mwarania told The Standard.  The police boss said unfortunately the woman in her 20's also died while receiving treatment.  The bodies have been moved to Machakos Level Five Hospital mortuary.  The vehicles have been towed to Salama Police Station yard as police launch investigations into the cause of the accident.   By Stephen Nzioka | 10 hours ago By Ali Abdi | 2 days ago By Gerald Mutethia | 2 days ago By Muriithi Mugo | 4 days ago The final days of Chris Kirubi